18/03/2005
BUCHAREST.
Romania -- The government hopes to wrap up talks on the stand-by agreement with the IMF by the middle of the year, according to a government statement issued on Thursday (17 March).
A finance ministry team has been invited to the IMF/World Bank meeting in the second half of April to continue talks on signing the agreement.
The government and the Fund have reached agreement on the budget deficit for the year, dispelling concerns that talks had stalled.
(Rompres - 18/03/05)
